SBC Email Handler Deployment Notes (GCP Cloud Functions Gen 2)

1) Go to the function project folder
cd d:/OneDrive/Documents/projects/SBC/SBC-Landing/email-handler

2) Prepare local deploy settings
- Copy deploy.local.env.example to deploy.local.env
- Fill in PROJECT_ID and any overrides (REGION, FUNCTION_NAME, etc.)

Example deploy.local.env values:
PROJECT_ID="your-gcp-project-id"
REGION="us-west1"
FUNCTION_NAME="contact-us-email-handler"
RUNTIME="nodejs20"
ENTRY_POINT="contactUsEmailHandler"
ENV_FILE="env.production.yaml"
ALLOW_UNAUTH="true"

3) Prepare production function environment variables
- Copy env.production.yaml.example to env.production.yaml
- Fill in real values

Required env.production.yaml keys:
RESEND_API_KEY: "replace_with_resend_api_key"
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL: "Sound Building Components <contact@yourdomain.com>"
CONTACT_TO_EMAIL: "your-inbox@yourdomain.com"
ALLOWED_ORIGIN: "https://sbc-landing-three.vercel.app"

Optional keys:
LIVE_ALLOWED_ORIGIN: "https://www.soundbuildingcomponents.com"
ALLOWED_ORIGINS: "https://sbc-landing-three.vercel.app,https://www.soundbuildingcomponents.com"

4) Deploy
npm run deploy:gcp

5) Get the function URL
gcloud functions describe contact-us-email-handler --gen2 --region=us-west1 --project=your-gcp-project-id --format="value(serviceConfig.uri)"

6) Wire frontend to the deployed function URL
- In Gatsby env, set:
GATSBY_CONTACT_FORM_ENDPOINT=<function-url-from-step-5>
- Rebuild and redeploy frontend.

7) Verify
- Submit the Contact Us form in production.
- Confirm email arrives at CONTACT_TO_EMAIL.

8) If needed, check function logs
gcloud functions logs read contact-us-email-handler --gen2 --region=us-west1 --project=your-gcp-project-id --limit=50

Operational notes
- Do not commit .env, deploy.local.env, or env.production.yaml.
- Rotate RESEND_API_KEY immediately if it was ever exposed.
- Use a verified sending domain in Resend for production delivery.
